2026-05-02 | Earliest Time to Finish One Land Ride and One Water Ride

	Question
Return the earliest possible finishing time.
	Key Insight
For every pair of rides:
		Land i
		Water j
We only need to evaluate two possibilities:
		1. Land → Water
		2. Water → Land
and take the minimum finish time.
For Land → Water:
		landFinish =
				landStart + landDuration
		waterBegin =
				max(landFinish, waterStart)
		totalFinish =
				waterBegin + waterDuration
Similarly for Water → Land.
	Approach
1.	Initialize answer = infinity.
2.	For every land ride i.
3.	For every water ride j.
4.	Compute:
		Land → Water finish time.
5.	Compute:
		Water → Land finish time.
6.	Update minimum answer.
7.	Return answer.
	Time Complexity
	O(L × W)
	where:
		L = number of land rides
		W = number of water rides
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int earliestFinishTime(vector<int>& landStartTime,
                           vector<int>& landDuration,
                           vector<int>& waterStartTime,
                           vector<int>& waterDuration) {
        int n = landStartTime.size();
        int m = waterStartTime.size();
        long long ans = LLONG_MAX;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for(int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                // Land -> Water
                long long landFinish =
                    (long long)landStartTime[i] +
                    landDuration[i];
                long long waterBegin =
                    max(landFinish,
                        (long long)waterStartTime[j]);
                ans = min(ans,
                          waterBegin +
                          waterDuration[j]);
                // Water -> Land
                long long waterFinish =
                    (long long)waterStartTime[j] +
                    waterDuration[j];
                long long landBegin =
                    max(waterFinish,
                        (long long)landStartTime[i]);
                ans = min(ans,
                          landBegin +
                          landDuration[i]);
            }
        }
        return (int)ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Since exactly one ride from each category must be chosen, every valid solution is determined by:
		(one land ride, one water ride)
and only two possible orders exist. Evaluating both orders for every pair and taking the minimum gives the earliest finishing time.
